tion on the markets. The examination of this dynamic and its consequences also leads to the question of how destructive the distributive forces of digital capitalism might be.  afunded by Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCapitalism. 0aEconomicsxData processing. 0aSocial sciences. 4aCapitalism. 4aEconomic Sociology. 4aEconomy. 4aSociology of Technology. 4aSociology. 4aTechnology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aCapitalism.  aEconomic Sociology.  aEconomy.  aSociology of Technology.  aSociology.  aTechnology.2 aDeutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z978311076851040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839458938?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839458938zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839458938/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076851-0 transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022b2022  